        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Upholstery Care and Cleaning Recommendations</title>
            <para>The upholstery vendor has supplied a list of solvents that are safe to use when cleaning the
                upholstery. These solvents, if properly used, will not harm the finish of the material. These solvents
                include:
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Denatured Ethyl Alcohol</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>VM&#38;P Naphtha</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Odorless Mineral Spirits</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Isopropyl Alcohol</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>
                <title>Recommended Cleaning Instructions</title>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Wash with mild soap and hot water to remove ordinary dirt, grime, etc.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Stubborn stains should be cleaned with alcohol. Odorless Mineral Spirits or VM&#38;P
                    Naphtha can be used to remove paint, tar, gum, shoe polish, etc. if alcohol does not remove the
                    stain.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Isopropyl Alcohol and Denatured Alcohol are especially recommended for cleaning stubborn
                    dirt and stains.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Never clean upholstery with polish remover, Graffiti Eater, strong caustic or acidic
                    agents or any cleaners with active solvents like MEK, Tolual, gasoline, etc.
                </para>
            </step1>
